text: The 1933–34 UCLA Bruins men's basketball team represented the University of California, Los Angeles during the 1933–34 NCAA men's basketball season and were members of the Pacific Coast Conference. The Bruins were led by 13th year head coach Caddy Works. They finished the regular season with a record of 10–13 and were fourth in the southern division with a record of 2–10. ==Previous season== The Bruins finished the regular season with a record of 10–11 and were fourth in the southern division with a record of 1–10. ==Roster== ==Schedule== |- !colspan=9 style=|Regular Season Source ==References== Category:UCLA Bruins men's basketball seasons Ucla UCLA Bruins Basketball UCLA Bruins Basketball
